<p><a name="Articles_on_communitarianism" id="Articles_on_communitarianism"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Communitarianism&amp;action=edit&amp;section=19" title="Edit section: Articles on communitarianism">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Articles on communitarianism</span></h3>
<p>Some potentially useful references, transported from the <a href="http://www.sourcewatch.org/wiki.phtml?title=Communitarianism" class="external text" title="http://www.sourcewatch.org/wiki.phtml?title=Communitarianism" rel="nofollow">Sourcewatch</a>, which also links additional articles of relevance to this topic:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.janda.org/b20/News%20articles/GW%2C%20the%20Communitarian.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.janda.org/b20/News%20articles/GW%2C%20the%20Communitarian.htm" rel="nofollow">GW Bush, a Communitarian?</a></li>
<li><a href="http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/communitarianism" class="external text" title="http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/communitarianism" rel="nofollow">Communitarianism</a> entry in the <i><a href="/wiki/Stanford_Encyclopedia_of_Philosophy" title="Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy">Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy</a></i> by Daniel Bell</li>
<li><a href="http://www.comunitarismo.it/" class="external text" title="http://www.comunitarismo.it/" rel="nofollow">Articles on communitarianism</a> ((ita icon))</li>
<li><a href="http://www.infed.org/biblio/communitarianism.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.infed.org/biblio/communitarianism.htm" rel="nofollow">"Communitarianism"</a>, <i>Infed</i> Encyclopedia.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Fareed_Zakaria" title="Fareed Zakaria">Fareed Zakaria</a>, <a href="http://slate.msn.com/id/2380" class="external text" title="http://slate.msn.com/id/2380" rel="nofollow">The ABCs of Communitarianism. A devil's dictionary</a>, <i>Slate</i>, July 26, 1996.</li>
<li>Robert Putnam, <a href="http://discover.npr.org/features/feature.jhtml?wfId=1118012" class="external text" title="http://discover.npr.org/features/feature.jhtml?wfId=1118012" rel="nofollow">Communitarianism</a>, <a href="/wiki/National_Public_Radio" title="National Public Radio">National Public Radio</a>, February 5, 2001: "The term 'Third Way' was used to describe President Clinton's form of liberalism. Now 'Communitarianism' is being used in the same way to describe President Bush's form of conservatism. They're both an attempt to create a middle ground...an alternative to the liberal-conservative paradigm."</li>
<li><a href="http://www.cpn.org/tools/dictionary/communitarian.html" class="external text" title="http://www.cpn.org/tools/dictionary/communitarian.html" rel="nofollow">"Civil Practices Network"</a></li>
</ul>
<p><br /></p>
